name: Kim San Leng Food Centre Bukit Panjang

reviews.text: Great food. Good variety. Drinks uncle or auntie will go round to help order drinks. Food is self-service. Place is adequately clean, but both ends of the food centre reeks of trash. Adequate ceiling fans to keep ventilation flowing amidst the humid weather. Stall owner and service staff are all friendly. SGQR is accepted across all stalls.

This KSL drink helper is very attentive compare to Bishan KSL! Thumb up for the both anuty that keep going around asking customer what to drink. And Teh O no sugar only cost $1. Many good food staff here like King of fried rice, Koo Kee Yong Toe Foo... Etc! If around this area will come again!
